      "strengths_deep_dive": [
        "Support Life Foundation demonstrates a commitment to operational leaness. By maintaining <cite id=\"9\">zero fundraising costs</cite>, the charity maximizes the impact of every dollar donated. Its financial health is further bolstered by <cite id=\"7\">7.1 months of working capital</cite>, which allows the organization to navigate unexpected economic shifts without immediate program disruption. This fiscal discipline is paired with a <cite id=\"6\">Platinum Seal of Transparency</cite>, the highest level offered by Candid, ensuring donors have access to comprehensive organizational data."
      ],
      "summary": "Founded in <cite id=\"1\">2017</cite>, Support Life Foundation is a community-based organization dedicated to social and economic justice. The charity focuses on providing programs that minimize costs while serving underserved populations in the <cite id=\"2\">United States, Sierra Leone, and Cameroon</cite>. In the 2023 fiscal year, the organization reported <cite id=\"3\">total revenue of $1,228,678</cite>, which was primarily driven by public contributions. Support Life Foundation operates with a lean financial model, maintaining an <cite id=\"4\">exceptional program expense ratio of 95.1%</cite>. This efficiency ensures that the vast majority of donor funds directly support its diverse initiatives, ranging from <cite id=\"5\">hot meals and health centers</cite> to educational support. The organization has achieved a <cite id=\"6\">Platinum Seal of Transparency from Candid</cite>, reflecting a high level of public disclosure. While it maintains <cite id=\"7\">7.1 months of working capital</cite>, providing strong short-term financial resilience, the charity faces challenges with long-term revenue growth. Its <cite id=\"8\">3-year revenue CAGR stands at -22.8%</cite>, suggesting a need for more diversified or sustainable funding streams to maintain its current scale of operations.",
